ging onto outmoded drone troopships, to be sent back whence they came. Even for such a crime as they had commited, they did not deserve extermination after their capture. &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br><br>Quite. <br><br>&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Rhyekki, have you found the refugees yet?&quot; She asked, turning away from the long line of evictees and staring into the night.<br><br>&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Yes. Twenty-nine parts. Hidden dense thicket patch. Not your jump-jets, frightening.&quot; The scout announced, the translation worse than usual due to his hushed voice.<br><br>&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Confirmed.&quot; Serra sighed, then broke into a trot towards the open savannah.<br>&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp *&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp *&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp *<br><br>&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The thicket bush was a green hell, brambles and spines that clawed at hair and face, and rasped against her armor.  The falling darkness compounded it, making the tunnelway into a claustrophobic vegetable bowel, scraping and scratching as she burrowed deeper.<br>&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>Even her night vision was hampered, the lack of light and heat giving her only dim impressions of the tunnelway.<br>&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>Fortunately, a goodly twenty meters into the brush, she began to sense light ahead.<br>&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>Nervously, she crawled onward, toward the nest space. In preparation, she began to practice the translation matrix as she emerged from the tunnel and into the dome-shaped dwelling area.<br>&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>Shrieking in fright or suprise, two of the natives leapt away as she emerged, while several more leapt forward, levelling short spears, some with metal blades, at her.<br>&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Of all the stupid ideas...</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> She thought to herself, painfully aware that with her helmet open she was vulnerable 