ot; The elder interrogated immediately, clutching a bone staff with one arm as it gestured at Serra.<br><br>&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;I am <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Serra'ki</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. I am enemy of the you'man. My people are enemy of the you'man. We fight the you'man, because they hurt you- people.&quot; Serra announced, the loremaster in her rising to the occasion.<br><br>&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;You'mans were strong like <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> gods!</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> They helped us! You stronger if destroy them, but why? They give their magic to us, make us strong like them!&quot; The elder chittered, producing a solar-powered light and waving its beam around the den.<br><br>&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;They had shells like you, and they knew <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> strong</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> magic.&quot; The elder continued, tapping on Serra's armor with his staff.<br><br>&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Yes. But they made their shells and learned their 'magic' on their own.&quot; She replied levelly, using a hand gesture to indicate that she conceded to his argument<br>&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br> &quot;You do not understand. You are weakened by their magic.&quot; Serra intoned resolutely, meeting the elders' gaze and holding it.<br>&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>There were murmurs of fear from the gathered pack, and one spearhunter screamed and threw his metal-tipped weapon to the ground.<br>&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>&quot;They make you weak. If you did not have to find food, and had all the food you needed when you wanted, you would become a weak hunter. The you'mans would do the same, and more, and make you weak.&quot;<br>&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>&quot;But how will we get their magic? You-people destroy the you'man things with fire from the sky and your own magic, and the metal-things you ride find the bones-pieces and take those away too!&quot; he asked, the translator annotating 